      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make the Juicy Pulled Chipotle Chicken."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the red onion and add to a bowl. Squeeze over the juice of half the lime, season with salt and set aside to pickle."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely chop the coriander, saving a few whole leaves for garnish. Crumble the feta and have your guac and crispy corn ready."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Reheat the rice and chipotle chicken in separate saucepans until piping hot. Stir the chopped coriander through the hot rice and squeeze over the juice of the remaining lime."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Build your bowls: start with a layer of coriander rice, then add pulled chipotle chicken, crumbled feta, spoonfuls of guac, pickled onions and a good handful of crunchy corn. Garnish with coriander leaves and serve with a lime wedge."
    }
